A postmortem conducted on the late IEBC ICT manager Chris Musando s remains has revealed that he was strangled to death.The autopsy was conducted by the Government Chief Pathologist Johansen Oduor and Bessie Byakika for the family at the Lee Funeral Home. Strangulation was the cause of death, Dr Odour said.It is not yet clear whether a postmortem has been conducted on his lady friend, Carol Ngumbu.The two bodies were found in a thicket in Kikuyu, 400 metres apart. They were both naked.Investigations are on going. The President has called for patience as the police find the people responsible for the deaths.Chris will be buried on 19 August in Ugenya.